{{Quote|There were twelve of us, including several high ranking commanders: High General Ajunta Pall; Marchioness XoXann, commanding the Black Legions; Baron Dreypa, our fleet's sole remaining admiral; Karness Muur, whose Force-centered battle tactics had saved us from the trap at Fluwhaka; and I, Sorzus Syn, grower of living weapons and biological plagues.|[[Sorzus Syn]]|<ref name="BoS">''[[Book of Sith: Secrets from the Dark Side]]''</ref>}}
The '''Exiles''', or ''[[Jen'jidai]]'' in the [[Sith (language)|Sith language]], were the twelve [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] leaders banished by the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] into the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]] after the [[Hundred-Year Darkness/Legends|Hundred-Year Darkness]]. The Exiles would eventually settle on [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]], conquer the [[Sith Empire (Pre-Republic)|Sith Empire]] and replace it with their [[Sith Empire/Legends|own]], and establish the [[Sith/Legends|Sith Order]] to reign over it. The most powerful among the Exiles were [[High General]] [[Ajunta Pall]], [[Marchioness]] and [[Black Legions]] commander [[XoXaan]], [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Baron/Legends|Baron]] [[Remulus Dreypa]], [[Karness Muur]], and [[Sorzus Syn]], high ranking commanders during the war against the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]]. Less important [[Dark Jedi faction (Doomed)|Dark Jedi]] followed Remulus Dreypa when he decided to depart the [[Stygian Caldera]], only to be found by [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] veterans of the [[Battle of Corbos]], resulting in a chase that ended with both factions banding together after a terrible battle on [[Kesh/Legends|Kesh]].

==Exile==
{{Quote|The Jedi, so confident in their triumph, did not execute us. With lightsaber points at our backs, they marched us aboard the galleon that would take us into exile, outside the Republic's borders.|[[Sorzus Syn]]|<ref name="BoS" />}}
[[File:Exodus1.jpg|thumb|left|200px|The Exiles being loaded into an unarmed galleon.]]
In [[6900 BBY]] the [[Hundred-Year Darkness/Legends|Hundred-Year Darkness]] ended with the defeat of the [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] at the [[Battle of Corbos]]. The Dark Jedi were forced onto an unarmed<ref name="JvS" /> [[Dark Jedi galleon|galleon]] and exiled beyond known space.<ref name="BoS" />

==Jen'ari==
{{Quote|I was one of many. We were servants of the dark side. Sith Lords, we called ourselves... So proud. In the end, we were not so proud.|[[Ajunta Pall]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''</ref>}}
[[File:ExiledDarkJedi-BoS.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Escorted by XoXaan, Sorzus Syn, and Remulus Dreypa, Ajunta Pall arrives on Korriban.]]

The Exiles were guided through the [[Stygian Caldera]] by [[Sorzus Syn]], who had spent years collecting rumors about the legendary [[Sith Empire (Pre-Republic)|Kingdom of the Sith]], and they eventually reached [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]], a planet strong in the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]] and home to the [[Sith (species)/Legends|Sith]] people. Upon [[Discovery of Korriban|arrival]], they awed the Sith with their power over the dark side, who named them the ''[[Jen'jidai]]''. The Exiles forged an alliance with the [[Shadow Hand]] to gain the confidence of [[Sith King]] [[Hakagram Graush]], whom their leader, [[Ajunta Pall]], promptly beheaded. Now in control, they appointed themselves Lords of the Sith, with Pall being granted the title of ''[[Jen'ari]]'', or [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]].<ref name="BoS" />

Some of the Exiles, however, were not satisfied to rule the Sith and wait to gather their strength. Within a year, some Dark Jedi returned to Republic space to [[First battle between Jedi and Sith|attack the Jedi]]. Their premature actions served only to alert the Republic and their defenders that some of the Exiles survived and taken control of a region called [[Sith Worlds/Legends|Sith Space]]. Those who remained behind<ref name="JvS" /> used their alchemical arts to blend their DNA with that of the Sith,<ref name="evil">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/88/indexp2.html|text=''Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties''|int=Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties}}</ref> allowing their lineage to continue through the Sith species. Following their takeover of Korriban, the Exiles reformed into the [[Sith Order]] and established the [[Sith Empire/Legends|Sith Empire]].<ref name="JvS" />

